// plugin.proto defines the OPEN probe/tool plugin protocol AND the OPEN
// collection-capability contract (D-0011).
//
// A plugin is an in-process collector the open agent can invoke to collect an
// additional class of evidence (e.g. a new exporter, a custom dmesg parser, a
// read-only eBPF observer). Plugins are read-only producers of EvidencePack
// fragments. They run off-critical-path and MUST NOT control, orchestrate, or
// checkpoint GPUs. This protocol is OPEN by design so third parties can audit
// every probe in the agent's source.
//
// D-0011 capability model: the closed controlplane NEVER pushes code or
// playbooks. It selects from the agent's FIXED, OPEN, SIGNED, vetted capability
// catalog by sending a declarative CollectDirective that names a
// CapabilityDescriptor by id. Describe advertises the catalog (handshake); the
// directive rides in the controlplane's RESPONSE to the agent's outbound HTTPS
// (zero inbound to the node). Consent tiers + resource budgets are enforced by
// the agent, the sole policy enforcer.
//
// Shared schema note: the gate's independence class (SignalSource) and the
// citable-signal/fault-class adjudication schema live in signal.proto /
// verdict.proto and are SHARED across the open rca library and the closed
// controlplane — this file references SignalSource for routing/independence and
// adds no adjudication logic of its own.

